SENATE RESOLUTION 241
By Oliver
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of John Louis Hayes, Jr., of
Madison.
WHEREAS, the members of this legislative body were greatly saddened to learn of the
passing of John Louis Hayes, Jr.; and
WHEREAS, Louis Hayes was a highly respected member of his community and a
consummate professional who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for his fellow
citizens in numerous capacities; and
WHEREAS, the eldest of eleven children, Mr. Hayes was born in Nashville on November
16, 1933, to John L. Hayes, Sr., and Louise Hayes Burnette; and
WHEREAS, he attended North High School until he enlisted in the United States Navy,
serving three years of active duty aboard the USS Cape Esperance during the Korean War era
and continuing his commitment in the naval reserve for more than twenty additional years; and
WHEREAS, following his military service, Louis Hayes served with acumen and alacrity
with Atlantic Envelope in Nashville and later distinguished himself in the field of restaurant
management; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Hayes also dedicated his time and talents to his faith community,
serving with diligence as the bookkeeper for St. Joseph Catholic Church until his retirement; and
WHEREAS, deeply devoted to his family, he was actively involved in coaching his sons'
baseball teams in the 1970s, and he especially enjoyed spending time outdoors fishing with his
six boys; and
WHEREAS, Louis Hayes was also an avid Atlanta Braves fan and a lover of
photography and reading, interests he pursued with enthusiasm throughout his life; and
